  "texts": [
    "For feature extraction, they used count vector, word-level TF-IDF, character-level TF-IDF, and n-gram-level TF-IDF.",
    "They chose the best classifier based on performance, which was trained in the manually annotated dataset to automatically annotate the remaining unlabeled dataset as false and real.",
    "The study used six classifiers, including RF, NB, LR, Multilayer Perceptron (MLP), XGB, and SVM.",
    "As a result, LR exhibited the best performance for both manual and automatic annotated datasets, which registered an F1-score of 93.3%.",
    "In this study, the stemming and rooting techniques failed to increase the performance of the classifiers."
  ],
